rker, treat the total APL stat of enemy operatives that contest it as 1 lower if at least one of those enemy operatives is within 3\" of friendly REIVER operatives.\nNote this is not a change to the APL stat, so any changes are cumulative with this.'),('IMP','PHO24','PHO24','RVRWAR','VG','Vanguard','Once per turning point, one friendly PHOBOS STRIKE TEAM operative with this rule can perform the Pick Up Marker or a mission action for 1 less AP.'),('IMP','SCT','SCT','HGNR','FORSCT','Forward Scouting','At the end of the Set Up Operatives step, you can select and resolve up to five Forward Scouting options. \nEach option has a number in brackets, which is the maximum of times you can select and resolve it from the battle.\nFor example, your five selections could be Recon x2, Trip Alarm, Booby Trap, and Diversion.\nIf both players have this ability, alternate resolving, starting with the Defender.\n<br/><br>\n<h5>Redeploy (5)</h5>\nChange the set up of one of your operatives that is wholly within your drop zone and/or change its order.\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Recon (2)</h5>\nResolve a Recon option as specified by the Scouting step of the mission sequence.\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Infiltrate (2)</h5>\nResolve an Infiltrate option as specified by the Scouting step of the mission sequence.\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Trip Alarm (2)</h5>\nPlace one of your Trip Alarm tokens anywhere in the killzone that is more than [PENT] from your opponent\'s drop zone.\nDuring the Firefight phase, the first time an enemy operative with a Conceal order moves within [CIRCLE] of one of your Trip Alarm tokens:\n<ul>\n<li>Remove that token</li>\n<li>Until the start of that enemy operative\'s next activation, friendly operatives treat it as if it has an Engage order.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Booby Trap (1)</h5>\nPlace one of your Booby Trap tokens more than [PENT] from your opponent\'s drop zone and more than [CIRCLE] from each objective marker.\nEach time an enemy operative moves within [CIRCLE] of one of your Booby Trap tokens, interrupt that action to roll 1D6, adding 1 to the result if the enemy operative\'s move is from a Charge or Dash action.\nOnly roll once per action for each relevant token.\n<ul>\n<li>On a 1-3, nothing happens and that enemy operative continues its action (the token is not removed)</li>\n<li>On a 4-6, that enemy operative suffers a number of Mortal Wounds equal to the result of the D6, its move action ends, and the token is removed</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Diversion (1)</h5>\nSelect one enemy operative. Subtract 1 from its APL.\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Devise Plan (1)</h5>\nYou gain 1 CP.\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Designate Target (1)</h5>\nSelect one enemy operative to gain your Target token.\nEach time a friendly SCOUT SQUAD operative fights in combat or makes a shooting attack against the enemy operative with your Target token,\nin the Roll Attack Dice step of that combat or shooting attack, you can re-roll one of your attack dice.'),('IMP','SCT','SCT','HNTR','FORSCT','Forward Scouting','At the end of the Set Up Operatives step, you can select and resolve up to five Forward Scouting options. \nEach option has a number in brackets, which is the maximum of times you can select and resolve it from the battle.\nFor example, your five selections could be Recon x2, Trip Alarm, Booby Trap, and Diversion.\nIf both players have this ability, alternate resolving, starting with the Defender.\n<br/><br>\n<h5>Redeploy (5)</h5>\nChange the set up of one of your operatives that is wholly within your drop zone and/or change its order.\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Recon (2)</h5>\nResolve a Recon option as specified by the Scouting step of the mission sequence.\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Infiltrate (2)</h5>\nResolve an Infiltrate option as specified by the Scouting step of the mission sequence.\n<br/><br/>\n<h5>Trip Alarm (2)</h5>\nPlace one of your Trip Alarm tokens anywhere in the killzone that is more than [PENT] from your opponent\'s drop zone.\nDuring the Firefight phase, the first time an enem